00:42:35,332 --> 00:42:37,672
But when I know that, OK, we just got 50 kids in there,

788
00:42:37,712 --> 00:42:39,793
and 45 of them all love this character,

789
00:42:40,373 --> 00:42:42,454
that's pretty good in my book.

790
00:42:42,994 --> 00:42:43,934
Avoid anecdotal stuff.

791
00:42:44,054 --> 00:42:45,155
Use good data.

792
00:42:45,315 --> 00:42:46,935
And create as many opportunities to get the

793
00:42:46,975 --> 00:42:47,775
feedback as possible.

794
00:42:47,795 --> 00:42:50,536
The more and more you ask feedback from someone, the

795
00:42:50,596 --> 00:42:52,537
less they're going to feel like they need to swing by

796
00:42:52,577 --> 00:42:55,298
your desk at 6 o'clock on a Friday to tell you about it.

797
00:42:55,558 --> 00:42:56,918
Because they know that you're listening.

798
00:42:56,938 --> 00:42:58,979
They know that you're going to come back to them.

799
00:42:59,339 --> 00:43:00,959
And really track that character's history.

